> For this vegetarian dinner recipe, you'll toss hunks of cheese directly into a hot pan. Yes, this technique took us by surprise too, but it's all about the halloumi—a sturdy Middle Eastern "grilling cheese" that's built for this treatment. It turns out, it IS easy being cheesy!

== Tomato-Cucumber Salad ==

Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Tomato{1} into ¼-inch pieces. Trim and finely dice @Mini Cucumber{1}. Roughly chop @Dill{1/4%ounce}. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, cucumber, @Golden Raisins{1%ounce}, and a pinch of dill; season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

== Pickled Carrots ==

Trim, peel, and slice @Carrot{3%ounce} lengthwise into ¼-inch-thick planks. Cut planks lengthwise into ¼-inch-thick matchsticks (ours were 3 inches long).

In a second small microwave-safe bowl, combine carrot, @Sugar{1%teaspoon}, juice from half the lemon, a pinch of salt, and pepper. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{30%seconds}. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

== Creamy Dill Sauce ==

In a third small bowl, combine @Sour Cream{4.5%tablespoon}, a big pinch of dill, and a big pinch of lemon zest. Add @?Water{1%teaspoon} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

== Grilling Cheese ==

Cut @Grilling Cheese{6%ounce} into 8 slices. Place @Za'atar Spice{1%tablespoon} on a #plate{}; season with salt and pepper. Coat cheese in seasoning, pressing to adhere. Shake off any excess seasoning.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium-high heat. (Be careful of oil splatter when adding the cheese!) Add grilling cheese and cook until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} per side. (For 4 servings, you may need to cook in batches, adding a drizzle of oil per batch.) Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

== Assembly ==

Meanwhile, wrap @Pita Bread{2} in a damp #paper towel{} and microwave until warm, ~{30%seconds}. Once cool enough to handle, halve pitas; gently pull apart to create pockets.

Spread insides of pitas with half the sauce. Evenly fill with pickled carrot (draining first), grilling cheese, remaining sauce, and as much tomato-cucumber salad as you like. Drizzle with @Hot Sauce{1%teaspoon} to taste.

Divide grilling cheese–stuffed pitas and any remaining tomato-cucumber salad between plates. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.